{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Arcadie'' (webcomic)}} {{Infobox comic strip |title=Arcadie | image= Arcadie_postindustrial_man.png |caption=Panel from "Post-industrial Man"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://arcadie.net/comic/5/|title=Arcadie: Post-industrial Man|publisher=arcadie.net}}</ref> (#5) |author=Ties Wijnker |url=[https://arcadie.net/ arcadie.net] |first=May 17, 2016<ref>{{cite web|url=http://arcadie.net/comic/1/|title= The Tragedy of Venn-Diagram Man|date= May 17, 2016|first=Ties|last=Wijnker|accessdate=September 4, 2016|work=Arcadie|publisher=www.arcadie.net}}</ref> |genre=[[Alternative comics|Alternative]], [[Black humor]], [[Surreal humor]] }} '''''Arcadie''''' is an English [[webcomic]] created by Dutch artist Ties Wijnker. Described in its tagline as "Comics for people," ''Arcadie'' revolves around a broad range of subjects, often dealing with the conditions and experiences of individual characters within modern life.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ovelhasvoadoras.com.br/2016/09/retrato-homem-moderno.html|title= Essa tirinha é um retrato do "homem moderno"|date= September 2, 2016|accessdate=September 6, 2016|work=Ovelhas Voadoras|publisher=www.ovelhasvoadoras.com.br}}</ref> Recurrent themes include [[irony]], [[technology]], [[entertainment]], [[boredom]], [[Social alienation|alienation]], and [[Fantasy (psychology)|fantasy]]. Many of the comics contain absurd or [[surrealist]] characters and premises, and they often lack a clear plot or traditional punchline.
== Style and format ==
''Arcadie'' features self-contained comics, with characters and settings changing per comic. They are organized in a single-page format, with the amount of [[Panel (comics)|panels]] per comic ranging from three to several dozen. Every comic comes with an additional short text placed under it, elaborating on its ideas. The artwork consists of digital linework and coloring with little shading, producing a [[minimalist]] aesthetic.
